        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Ok..I am probably missing something, so i'm sure someone here will be happy to point out where I'm being stupid.</P><P>The other day, I saw an epic Nec in Lich form swapping out the Scythe for Zlands heart to med.  While, initially this seemed to make sense, I began to wonder.  When you remove the Scythe, you immediately drop 20 intel which is about 200 mana.  Wouldn't that loss more than offset the +5 hp regen from the heart.</P><P>Even assuming because of the PvP glitch with Lich that we get a 1:1 return from health to mana, it seems that the 200 mana lost from removing the sythe would take the heart 40 ticks to make up.</P><P>Seems...it would be better just to keep the scythe equipped...what am I missing?</P><P>ta,<BR>=SV=</P><P> </font></td>
