        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Because changes in INT and also from +MANA only affect the maximum amount of mana you can hold, not the current amount of mana you have.</P><P>IE if you have 1200 mana out of 4000, and take off 2000 mana worth of gear and put it back on, you will still have 1200 mana.</P><P>So swapping out the heart doesn't cost you any mana unless you are nearly FM anyway.  After you med back up swap it back in and you're gtg with less hp lost from liching than you would have otherwise.</P><P>PS.  Assuming by scythe you meant our epic, both it and the heart have 20 INT on them, the only difference between them manawise is the direct +80 mana from the epic.  This isn't a heck of a lot to be short of FM at the levels where epic and heart are both in hand.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
